choices.text: You have a set of machines and a set of customers. Each customer can buy one second of CPU time or $Q$ seconds for some integer $Q$. Each time slot a customer purchases must be completed on a single machine, but you get to decide how to allocate the purchased time slots between machines. After coming back from a long vacation, you see that all of your machines are idle and a variety of orders have come in. To keep customers happy, you must decide how to distribute these requests between machines in a way that minimizes the time when the purchased time slots are finally all completed. What is the smallest amount of time in which you can complete all of the purchased time slots
